arguments.prompt:
You are building a Blazor Web App for construction site building inspectors. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-81cd0dc6c0c74d4696cf48476a0b20bd/SiteInspector/` with:
- Server project: `SiteInspector/SiteInspector/`
- Client project: `SiteInspector/SiteInspector.Client/`
- Global Interactive WebAssembly mode (already configured in App.razor)

## Requirements
- Inspectors fill out safety checklists and add notes at each site visit
- Photos are attached to inspection reports
- Offline-first: app must work without connectivity using IndexedDB
- When connectivity returns, data syncs back to the server
- Mobile-first (phones/tablets)
- Low-latency UI (fast tap-through of checklist items)
- No authentication

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Models (in Client project: `SiteInspector.Client/Models/`)

Create these model classes:

**Site.cs** - A construction site
```csharp
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Models;

public class Site
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Address { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
}
```

**Inspection.cs** - A site visit/inspection
```csharp
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Models;

public class Inspection
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string SiteId { get; set; } = "";
    public string SiteName { get; set; } = "";
    public DateTime InspectionDate { get; set; } = DateTime.UtcNow;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
    public List<ChecklistItem> ChecklistItems { get; set; } = new();
    public List<PhotoRecord> Photos { get; set; } = new();
    public bool IsSynced { get; set; }
    public InspectionStatus Status { get; set; } = InspectionStatus.InProgress;
}

public enum InspectionStatus
{
    InProgress,
    Completed
}
```

**ChecklistItem.cs** - Individual safety checklist items
```csharp
namespace SiteInspector.Client.Models;

public class ChecklistItem
{
    public string Id { get; set; } = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    public string Category { get; set; } = "";
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public ChecklistResult Result { get; set; } = ChecklistResult.NotInspected;
    public string Notes { get; set; } = "";
